shared_text:
Dunker Auction Service added 85 new photos to the album: BUILD Academy Online Fund Raising Auction.
July 29 at 12:30 AM ·

Auction starts Aug. 1 and will start ending at 5:30pm on Aug 6. The School District of Washington's BUILD Academy (Building Unique and Innovative Learning by Design) is held at Four Rivers Career Center.
BUILD Academy offers an authentic project based learning experience to over 100 sixth-grade students from Washington West Elementary and Campbellton Elementary. This project based learning model exposes students to possible careers that they may not even knew exist before they enter the BUILD Academy. The end project is a dog house. However, the true learning occurs when these students use every day standards by means of developing a business plan, designing business logos, drafting the dog house design from scratch and applying math and measuring skills to the actual building of the doghouse.
Go to www.dunkerauction.com to register and bid. Bid your price and if you’re the high bidder just show up at designated pick up time pay and take your items home. It really is that easy!!

Washington High School Senior Spotlight
Drew Post
President of Theatre Guild, Vice President of Choir, and President of the Improv Club. Member of the Principal's Advisory Board, Interact Club, STUCO, Leadership, A+, and DECA.
Favorite memory is performing as Gomez Addams in the WHS Theatre Guilds production of The Addams Family. We all became so close as a cast, we truly became a family. We all had such an amazing time performing the show and creating memories that will last us all a lifetime.
I plan on attending Southeast Missouri State University to achieve a degree in Performing Arts with a focus on Acting and Directing and minoring in either English or Business.

Washington High School Senior Spotlight
Hannah Eckelkamp
I am involved in Link Crew. As a freshman and sophomore, I was on the softball team.
My favorite high school memory was being on the JV softball team. There were countless moments where I laughed so hard I almost cried.
I babysit a lot, work at Moe’s Pizza Buffet, hang out with family and friends, play with my dogs, work out and stay healthy.
I plan to go to ECC for nursing. Then I would like to work in a hospital and get my BSN.
